## Phase 5: Frontend-Backend Integration Bug Fix (14:30 – 15:20)

### User report
> "the frontend is not connected to the backend while I refresh the data is updated"

### Investigation
1. Found frontend process on port 3000 (PID 16588)
2. Located frontend at: `C:\Users\Varun Kalyadapu\Downloads\issue-tracker-project\issue-tracker-project\issue-tracker-frontend\`
3. Examined `api.js` — correctly configured with `baseURL: "http://localhost:8080/api"` and all endpoints
4. **Examined `App.jsx` line 16:**
```javascript
const [issues, setIssues] = useState(SEED_ISSUES);  // ← HARDCODED!
```

### Root cause
The frontend had a complete `api.js` with correct endpoints, but **no page ever imported or used it**. All 5 pages used hardcoded `SEED_ISSUES` from `constants.js` and manipulated local React state.

### Fix — 5 files rewritten

**App.jsx:**
```diff
- import { SEED_ISSUES } from "./data/constants";
+ import { getIssues } from "./services/api";

- const [issues, setIssues] = useState(SEED_ISSUES);
+ const [issues, setIssues] = useState([]);
+ useEffect(() => { fetchIssues(); }, []);
+ const fetchIssues = async () => {
+   const res = await getIssues();
+   setIssues(res.data.map(i => ({ ...i, created_at: i.createdAt?.split("T")[0] })));
+ };
```

**CreateIssue.jsx:**
```diff
- setIssues((prev) => [issue, ...prev]);  // local only
+ await createIssue(form);                // real API POST
+ await fetchIssues();                    // reload from backend
```

**IssueDetail.jsx:**
```diff
- const [comments, setComments] = useState(SEED_COMMENTS[issue.id] || []);  // hardcoded
+ useEffect(() => { getComments(issue.id).then(res => setComments(res.data)); }, []);

- setIssues((prev) => prev.map(...));  // local status update
+ await updateIssueStatus(issue.id, status);  // real PATCH API

- setIssues((prev) => prev.filter(...));  // local delete
+ await deleteIssue(issue.id);  // real DELETE API

- setComments((prev) => [...prev, localComment]);  // local add
+ await postComment(issue.id, text);  // real POST API
```

**Kanban.jsx:**
```diff
- setIssues((prev) => prev.map(...));  // local state on drag
+ await updateIssueStatus(dragging.id, newStatus);  // real PATCH API
```

**Dashboard.jsx:**
```diff
- // CSV: client-side generation
+ const res = await exportIssuesCSV();  // real GET /api/issues/export

- // Simulate: fake local issue
+ await createIssue(issue);  // real POST to create an actual issue
```

